Vogue posting them is mainly due to the age of the woman in question wearing this outfit, which is quite unique of course. Acting like this is really amazing is just very fucking dumb

snippet.textDisplay: I remember when I was a kid (maybe 5-6 years old) I went to a place that was having a bunch of runway shows because my mom is involved in fashion. I didn’t bring much to keep myself warm so I told my mom and she had a turquoise cheetah print scarf. A few people asked to take photos of me including a guy from Oi which is a big company, sort of like t-mobile in my country. I also ended up on my country’s vogue website. I wanted to go see more runway shows but we’d already gone to all of the ones we had tickets for, but luckily a woman shows up and asks me if I’m the girl people had been taking pictures of. When I said yes she gave me a ticket for another one lol
